"Subject": "Item 11 - Adoption of the 2023 Mathematics Framework for California\nPublic Schools, Kindergarten Through Grade Twelve.",
"StanceontheMatter": "Oppose",
"Comments": "Dear Sirs,\n\nIf you design math education for kids who hate math, you\u2019re punishing kids who\nlike math. It\u2019s self-defeating, and that\u2019s what you\u2019re doing here.\n\nIf you want to solve the problem that elite college admission departments\nrequire too much calculus, you ought to take it up with elite college admission\ndepartments. They are, after all, the ones wholly in charge of elite college\nadmissions. Just limiting how much math you are willing to teach the California\nstudents who love math \u2013 and they exist! I was one! I am raising two! \u2013 is an\nabsurdly roundabout and likely totally ineffective way to achieve your stated\ngoals.\n\nInstead, I humbly suggest that you build more schools for the academically\ngifted, not fewer, and build them in minority neighborhoods, not in the San\nFernando Valley. And maybe change how the HGM admission testing works! There\u2019s\nnothing magic about the way you\u2019re doing it now.\n\nSincerely,\nLewis Morton\nParent of 2 kids in LAUSD",
